Forty manuscripts have been collated for this passage, which on account of its proximity would naturally be compared with the passage on fs.161- 162b. In the main the agreement is the same. For (Ι) we have OB, MA, ΜΒ, MD, MI, LC, CM, LF, LG, and possibly OM, HA, W, OG, Y. The smaller groups are (OB, LF, LG), (MA, MD), (ΜΙ, LC, CM). There is a question as to the position of the pair group HA, OM, which is found also with (ΙΙΙ). On fs. 161-162b, OM, HA, W, were seen to form a group. No such combination is visible here, perhaps because of the paucity of variants, or · from the fact that W has changed its hand in the interval.
